  { '@type': 'Question', name: 'Does elderberry really reduce cold duration?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Yes, according to the available clinical evidence. A 2019 meta-analysis of 4 RCTs found that elderberry supplementation reduced upper respiratory infection duration by an average of 1.86 days and significantly reduced symptom severity. A separate 2016 randomized, double-blind study of 312 air travelers found that those taking elderberry experienced significantly fewer cold days and less severe symptoms than the placebo group. While the evidence is promising, the total number of clinical trials is still relatively small, and larger confirmatory studies are needed. Elderberry appears most effective when started early — within 24-48 hours of symptom onset.' } },
