  { '@type': 'Question', name: 'Can children take elderberry gummies?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Most elderberry gummies are formulated for adults and children ages 4 and older. Some brands (like Zarbee\'s) specifically formulate pediatric versions for children ages 2 and up. Elderberry has a long history of use in children\'s folk medicine, and clinical studies have included children as young as 5 with no serious adverse effects. However, always use age-appropriate products at the recommended dose. Children under 2 should not take elderberry supplements. If your child has an autoimmune condition, consult their pediatrician before starting elderberry.' } },
